               <id root="2d4f877c-42f8-41b4-8f31-346dc4f88c25"/>
               <code code="34089-3" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="DESCRIPTION SECTION"/>
               <text>
                  <linkHtml href="#section-"/>DESCRIPTION<paragraph>Baclofen USP is a muscle relaxant and antispastic, available as 
10 mg and 20 mg tablets for oral administration. Its chemical name is 
4-amino-3-(4-chlorophenyl)-butanoic acid.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Baclofen USP is a white to off-white, odorless or practically odorless 
crystalline powder. It is slightly soluble in water, very slightly soluble in 
methanol, and insoluble in chloroform. The structural formula is represented 
below:</paragraph>
                  <paragraph> <renderMultiMedia referencedObject="MM1"/>    BACLOFEN STRUCTURE IIMAGE</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Baclofen Tablets USP 10 mg and 20 mg contain the following inactive ingredients: 
magnesium stearate, microcrystalline cellulose, povidone and starch (corn).</paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20100629"/>
